						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1526, Krōdhi, Pushya, ba. 3, Śukravāra,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1604 December 28, Friday, f.d.t. ·23,</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Veṅkaṭapatidēva-Mahārāya</hi> ruling at <hi rend="bold">[Penu]goṇḍe.</hi> It records that <hi rend="bold">Immaḍi-Raṅgapa-Nāyaka,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Lakshmīpati-Nāyaka-Raṅgapa-Nāyaka</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Harati,</hi> made a gift of the village <hi rend="bold">Rāviḍi</hi> situated in <hi rend="bold">Maduviḍisthala</hi> in <hi rend="bold">Agaḷi-sīme,</hi> a sub-division of <hi rend="bold">Rāyadurga-vēṇṭhe,</hi> to <hi rend="bold">Umāpati-Arasa,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Saṅkappayya</hi> and grandson of <hi rend="bold">Kōṭeya-Rāmarasayya,</hi> of Bhāradvāja-<hi rend="italic">gōtra,</hi> Āśvalāyana-<hi rend="italic">sūtra,</hi> and Ṛik-<hi rend="italic">śākhā.</hi></p>						

						<p>First face.</p>						

						</summary>
